    2	
    3	## Theme
    4	First-principles attack on O(polylog) prime computation, deliberately avoiding reading CLOSED_PATHS.md to force fresh thinking.
    5	
    6	## Approach
    7	Brainstormed 5 genuinely unconventional ideas inspired by barrier-breaking analogies:
    8	- Shor's algorithm (quantum Fourier transform)
    9	- Compressed sensing (sparsity assumptions)
    10	- Fast multipole method (hierarchical decomposition)
    11	- Matrix completion (nuclear norm relaxation)
    12	
    13	## Experiments
    14	
    15	### 1. Transfer Matrix Sieve (`experiments/wildcard/transfer_matrix_sieve.py`)
    16	**Idea:** Encode sieve as matrix product, iterate via repeated squaring.
    17	**Result:** State space = lcm(primes up to sqrt(x)) ~ exp(sqrt(x)). Even with blocking, work ~ 10^100 vs ML's 10^67 for x=10^100. Depth-k sieve reinvents Meissel-Lehmer.
    18	**Verdict:** FAIL (Equivalence)
    19	
    20	### 2. Wavelet/Fourier Compression (`experiments/wildcard/wavelet_zero_compression.py`, `wavelet_detrended.py`)
    21	**Idea:** If C(x) = pi(x) - li(x) is sparse in wavelets, evaluate at point using O(polylog) coefficients.
    22	**Result:** Raw signal: 99% energy in 1 coeff (DC artifact). Detrended: N^{0.75} coefficients for 99.9% energy. Power spectrum f^{-1.7} across all scales.
    23	**Verdict:** FAIL (Information). Sublinear compression but far from polylog.
    24	
    25	### 3. Modular Residue Prediction (`experiments/wildcard/modular_residue_prediction.py`)
    26	**Idea:** Predict p(n) mod q from n for all small q, then CRT to recover p(n).
    27	**Result:** Near-max entropy for q>2. CRT is circular. Primorial mod-210 shows 19x prediction from wheel structure, but not useful.
    28	**Verdict:** FAIL (Circularity + Information)
