    1137	### Key Insights
    1138	(a) **Carry propagation boundary** is the most novel measurement: the easy-to-hard transition
    1139	    in binary representation of p(n) is a ~4-bit-wide sigmoid at ~60% of bit positions.
    1140	    This quantifies exactly how R^{-1}(n) fails: it gets all MSBs right but the transition
    1141	    to random is sharp, leaving no room for hierarchical bit recovery.
